For reference, I have also tried
```js
module.exports = {
    entry: './main.js',
    output: {path: __dirname + '/app', filename: 'main.js'},
    target: 'electron-main',
    externalsPresets: {electron: true, electronMain: true, node: true}
};
```
which doesn't work either (electron/index.js is still bundled). Unless I'm missing anything, I suspect there is a bug in how `externalsPresets` are processed.

